'''Diepoxybutane''' (also known as '''butane diepoxide''', '''butadiene diepoxide''', or '''1,2:3,4-diepoxybutane''') is a chemical compound with two [[epoxide]] [[functional group]]s. It is used as a chemical intermediate, as a [[curing agent]] for [[polymer]]s, as a [[cross-linking agent]] for textiles, and as a [[preservative]].<ref name=roc>[http://ntp.niehs.nih.gov/ntp/roc/twelfth/profiles/Diepoxybutane.pdf Diepoxybutane] ''Report on Carcinogens, Twelfth Edition'' (2011)</ref>
Diepoxybutane is a [[carcinogen]].<ref name=roc/>
